[Student "S"]
{WEST has an mid-range 1NT opener; a balanced hand with 16 points.

EAST has 9 points. He bids 2NT, asking WEST to pass if she has 15 or bid 3NT if she has 17.

But WEST has 16 points, which leaves her with no clear choice. 
In this case she must decide whether her hand is a "good" 16 points or a "poor" 16 points. 
Since her supporting cards are mostly 10's, 9's and 8's she figures it as "good" 
and bids 3NT.}

